// These variables are used when there is a separate ldap for system admins. Not needed for step-by-step demo or Web Sample App Demo.

pm.environment.set("userMobileNumber", "+1< insert user's phone number for OTP notifications >");
pm.environment.set("userEmail", "< insert user's email for OTP notifications>@acme.com");

// These clients have their secrets dynamically generated by SSP and stored in Kubernetes secrets

// kubectl get secret ${RELEASENAME}-ssp-secret-defaulttenantclient -n ${NAMESPACE} -o jsonpath="{.data.clientId}" | base64 --decode; echo
// kubectl get secret ${RELEASENAME}-ssp-secret-systemclient -n ${NAMESPACE} -o jsonpath="{.data.clientId}" | base64 --decode; echo

//(NAMESPACE="${NAMESPACE}"; RELEASE="${RELEASENAME}"; for a in "defaultTenantClientID defaultTenantClientSecret defaulttenantclient" "infraClientID infraClientSecret infraclient" "systemClientID systemClientSecret systemclient" "clientId clientSecret democlient"; do read CI CS S < <(echo "$a"); for b in "${CI} clientId" "${CS} clientSecret"; do read C D < <(echo "$b"); echo "pm.environment.set(\"${C}\", \"$(kubectl get secret "${RELEASE}-ssp-secret-${S}" -n "${NAMESPACE}" -o jsonpath="{.data.${D}}" | base64 --decode)""\");"; done; done)
